# Sanad AI - Cursor Rules

## Project Structure
This is an Nx monorepo with the following structure:
- **Apps**: `apps/portal` (main application), `apps/sanad-ai` (library), `apps/muhallil-ahkam` (library)
- **Libraries**: Located in `libs/` directory
  - `libs/ui` - UI components (shadcn/ui + AI Elements)
  - `libs/api` - API client and React Query setup
  - `libs/chat` - Chat functionality (domain, streaming, data-access, ui)
  - `libs/config` - App registry and feature flags
  - `libs/markdown` - Markdown rendering
  - `libs/response-parser` - Response parsing utilities

## TypeScript & Imports
- Use TypeScript path aliases defined in `tsconfig.base.json`:
  - `@sanad-ai/ui` → `libs/ui/src/index.ts`
  - `@sanad-ai/api` → `libs/api/src/index.ts`
  - `@sanad-ai/config` → `libs/config/src/index.ts`
  - `@sanad-ai/chat/*` → `libs/chat/*/src/index.ts`
  - `@sanad-ai/markdown` → `libs/markdown/src/index.ts`
  - `@sanad-ai/response-parser` → `libs/response-parser/src/index.ts`
- Within `libs/ui`, use `@/*` alias for relative imports (e.g., `@/lib/utils`)

## Component Guidelines
- UI components are in `libs/ui/src/components/`
- AI Elements components are in `libs/ui/src/components/ai-elements/`
- Use shadcn/ui components as base, extend with AI Elements when needed
- Always use the `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
- Components should be typed with TypeScript interfaces

## Code Style
- Use React 18+ with functional components and hooks
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow existing patterns in the codebase
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (CSS Variables mode)
- Components should be self-contained and reusable

## Build System
- Use Nx for task running: `nx <target> <project>`
- Use Vite for building and dev server
- Libraries build to `dist/packages/`
- Apps build to `dist/apps/`
- Portal app dynamically loads other apps from `/packages/` path

## Development
- Run portal in dev mode: `nx serve portal` or `npm run dev:portal`
- Run individual apps: `npm run dev:sanad-ai` or `npm run dev:ahkam`
- Build libraries: `nx build <library-name>`
- Use Nx affected commands for efficient builds
- Hot module replacement is enabled in dev mode
- Environment variables: Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure:
  - `VITE_API_BASE_URL` - API base URL (default: `http://localhost:3000/api`)
  - `VITE_API_BASIC_AUTH_USERNAME` - Basic auth username (optional)
  - `VITE_API_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD` - Basic auth password (optional)
  - `VITE_API_BASIC_AUTH` - Pre-encoded base64 auth string (alternative to username/password)

## Testing
- Write tests alongside code
- Use Nx test targets: `nx test <project>`

## Git & Files
- Don't commit `node_modules/`, `dist/`, or build artifacts
- Don't commit `.env` files (use `.env.example` as template)
- Keep components.json and tsconfig files in sync between root and libs/ui

## AI Elements
- AI Elements components are from `https://registry.ai-sdk.dev/`
- Components use `@ai-elements` registry in components.json
- Don't try to install `@ai-elements/all` from npm (it's not available)
- Use individual component imports from `libs/ui/src/components/ai-elements/`

## Important Notes
- This is a micro-frontend architecture where portal loads apps dynamically
- Apps are built as libraries and exposed via global window objects
- Feature flags control which apps are enabled
- RTL (Right-to-Left) support is available in markdown renderer

